      "message": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "These five weeks exist to build the platform everything else stands on. Every exercise in this block was chosen to give your muscles maximum work with minimum wear on your joints and your recovery — because with your work life running at full throttle, training has to add to you, not drain you.",
          "Your only mental job this cycle: control. Lower every rep slowly, exactly as written, and log every weight you lift. Don't chase numbers yet — chase perfect reps and leave a little in the tank when the program says to.",
          "Do that, and by Week 5 the numbers rise on their own: heavier presses, a stronger lower body, and sessions that leave you sharper than they found you."
        ],
        "outcomes": [
          "Leg press load up 10–15% at the same effort",
          "Dumbbell bench press up at least 2 kg per hand",
          "Every lowering phase at full 3-second control — no shortcuts",
          "All 15 sessions completed and logged",
          "Split squats rock-steady — no knee wobble"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 2,
      "name": "Volume Engine",
      "tagline": "Work Becomes Muscle",
      "weeks": "Weeks 6–10",
      "focuses": [
